50|$|Prior to 1 January 1996, the UK's general {{copyright}} {{term was}} {{the life of}} the author plus 50 years. The extension, to {{the life of the}} author plus 70 years, was introduced by The <b>Duration</b> <b>of</b> <b>Copyright</b> and Rights in Performances Regulations 1995 (SI 1995/3297), implementing Council Directive No.93/98/EEC, to harmonise the <b>duration</b> <b>of</b> <b>copyright</b> throughout the European Economic Community.|$|E
